    "markdown": "# Ch. 1: Tasks & Quizzes {.unnumbered}\n---\n\n::: {.callout-tip collapse=\"false\"}\n#### Your turn! {.unnumbered}\n\nThis quiz encourages you to do some quick internet searches to find out more about open-source software.\n\n[**Q1.1**]{style=\"color:green;\"} Which of these is an open-source alternative to Microsoft Word?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<form name=\"form_Q1_1\" onsubmit=\"return validate_form_Q1_1()\" method=\"post\">\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_1\" id=\"answer_Q1_1_1\" value=\"LibreOffice Writer\"/>\nLibreOffice Writer\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_1\" id=\"answer_Q1_1_2\" value=\"Pages\"/>\nPages\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_1\" id=\"answer_Q1_1_3\" value=\"Google Docs\"/>\nGoogle Docs\n</label>\n<br/>\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Check answer\"/>\n<div id=\"result_Q1_1\"></div>\n</form>\n<script>function validate_form_Q1_1() {var x, text; var x = document.forms['form_Q1_1']['answer_Q1_1'].value;if (x == 'LibreOffice Writer'){text = 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Writer as part of the LibreOffice package.';} else {text = 'No, this software is not open source. The source code is not available to all.';} document.getElementById('result_Q1_1').innerHTML = text; evaluate_final_score(); return false;}function evaluate_final_score(){\n         element = document.getElementById('checkdown_final_score');\n         if(element === null){return false;} else {var element, text, res1;res1 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_1').innerText == 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Writer as part of the LibreOffice package.';text = res1;element.innerHTML = text;\n         return false;\n         }}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n[**Q1.2**]{style=\"color:green;\"} Which of these is an open-source alternative to Microsoft Powerpoint?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<form name=\"form_Q1_2\" onsubmit=\"return validate_form_Q1_2()\" method=\"post\">\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_2\" id=\"answer_Q1_2_1\" value=\"Keynote\"/>\nKeynote\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_2\" id=\"answer_Q1_2_2\" value=\"LibreOffice Impress\"/>\nLibreOffice Impress\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_2\" id=\"answer_Q1_2_3\" value=\"Google Slides\"/>\nGoogle Slides\n</label>\n<br/>\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Check answer\"/>\n<div id=\"result_Q1_2\"></div>\n</form>\n<script>function validate_form_Q1_2() {var x, text; var x = document.forms['form_Q1_2']['answer_Q1_2'].value;if (x == 'LibreOffice Impress'){text = 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Impress as part of the LibreOffice package.';} else {text = 'No, this software is proprietary.';} document.getElementById('result_Q1_2').innerHTML = text; evaluate_final_score(); return false;}function evaluate_final_score(){\n         element = document.getElementById('checkdown_final_score');\n         if(element === null){return false;} else {var element, text, res1, res2;res1 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_1').innerText == 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Writer as part of the LibreOffice package.'; res2 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_2').innerText == 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Impress as part of the LibreOffice package.';text = res1 + res2;element.innerHTML = text;\n         return false;\n         }}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n[**Q1.3**]{style=\"color:green;\"} Not only can software be open source, programming languages can, too. In fact, most modern programming languages are open source. In this book, we will focus on the open-source programming language `R`. Which of these is *not* an open-source programming language?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<form name=\"form_Q1_3\" onsubmit=\"return validate_form_Q1_3()\" method=\"post\">\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_3\" id=\"answer_Q1_3_1\" value=\"MATLAB\"/>\nMATLAB\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_3\" id=\"answer_Q1_3_2\" value=\"Python\"/>\nPython\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_3\" id=\"answer_Q1_3_3\" value=\"JavaScript\"/>\nJavaScript\n</label>\n<br/>\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Check answer\"/>\n<div id=\"result_Q1_3\"></div>\n</form>\n<script>function validate_form_Q1_3() {var x, text; var x = document.forms['form_Q1_3']['answer_Q1_3'].value;if (x == 'MATLAB'){text = 'Correct. MATLAB is one of the few genuinely closed-source programming languages that continue to be used in research.';} else {text = 'No, just like <code>R</code>, this programming language is also open source.';} document.getElementById('result_Q1_3').innerHTML = text; evaluate_final_score(); return false;}function evaluate_final_score(){\n         element = document.getElementById('checkdown_final_score');\n         if(element === null){return false;} else {var element, text, res1, res2, res3;res1 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_1').innerText == 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Writer as part of the LibreOffice package.'; res2 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_2').innerText == 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Impress as part of the LibreOffice package.'; res3 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_3').innerText == 'Correct. MATLAB is one of the few genuinely closed-source programming languages that continue to be used in research.';text = res1 + res2 + res3;element.innerHTML = text;\n         return false;\n         }}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n[**Q1.4**]{style=\"color:green;\"} There are also many open-source operating systems. Which of these is an open-source alternative to the operating system Windows?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<form name=\"form_Q1_4\" onsubmit=\"return validate_form_Q1_4()\" method=\"post\">\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_4\" id=\"answer_Q1_4_1\" value=\"iOS\"/>\niOS\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_4\" id=\"answer_Q1_4_2\" value=\"Ubuntu\"/>\nUbuntu\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_4\" id=\"answer_Q1_4_3\" value=\"MacOS\"/>\nMacOS\n</label>\n<br/>\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Check answer\"/>\n<div id=\"result_Q1_4\"></div>\n</form>\n<script>function validate_form_Q1_4() {var x, text; var x = document.forms['form_Q1_4']['answer_Q1_4'].value;if (x == 'Ubuntu'){text = 'Correct! Ubuntu is one of many Linux distributions, a family of open source operating systems. You can find out more here: <a href=\"https://itsfoss.com/getting-started-with-ubuntu/\">https://itsfoss.com/getting-started-with-ubuntu/</a>.';} else {text = 'No, this operating system is not open source. It is owned by Apple.';} document.getElementById('result_Q1_4').innerHTML = text; evaluate_final_score(); return false;}function evaluate_final_score(){\n         element = document.getElementById('checkdown_final_score');\n         if(element === null){return false;} else {var element, text, res1, res2, res3, res4;res1 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_1').innerText == 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Writer as part of the LibreOffice package.'; res2 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_2').innerText == 'Correct! And the good news is that, in Task 1 (see below), you will install LibreOffice Impress as part of the LibreOffice package.'; res3 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_3').innerText == 'Correct. MATLAB is one of the few genuinely closed-source programming languages that continue to be used in research.'; res4 = document.getElementById('result_Q1_4').innerText == 'Correct! Ubuntu is one of many Linux distributions, a family of open source operating systems. You can find out more here: https://itsfoss.com/getting-started-with-ubuntu/.';text = res1 + res2 + res3 + res4;element.innerHTML = text;\n         return false;\n         }}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n::: {.callout-tip collapse=\"false\"}\n#### Your turn! {.unnumbered}\n\n[**Q1.5**]{style=\"color:green;\"} Is it possible to reuse @fig-OER on a company website?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<form name=\"form_Q1_5\" onsubmit=\"return validate_form_Q1_5()\" method=\"post\">\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_5\" id=\"answer_Q1_5_1\" value=\"Yes, but you must mention the image&#39;s sell-by date.\"/>\nYes, but you must mention the image's sell-by date.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_5\" id=\"answer_Q1_5_2\" value=\"Yes, but you must mention the name of the artist.\"/>\nYes, but you must mention the name of the artist.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_5\" id=\"answer_Q1_5_3\" value=\"Yes, but only after having obtained written consent from the artist.\"/>\nYes, but only after having obtained written consent from the artist.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q1_5\" id=\"answer_Q1_5_4\" value=\"Yes, but only if it is the website of a non-profit company.\"/>\nYes, but only if it is the website of a non-profit company.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Check answer\"/>\n<div id=\"result_Q1_5\"></div>\n</form>\n<script>function validate_form_Q1_5() {var x, text; var x = document.forms['form_Q1_5']['answer_Q1_5'].value;if (x == 'Yes, but you must mention the name of the artist.'){text = 'That’s right!';} else {text = 'No, that’s not what the CC-BY license means.';} document.getElementById('result_Q1_5').innerHTML = text